1月4日，在尚无确诊病例的情况下，香港卫生署启动应变计划，将应变等级从“戒备”升为“严重”。
On January 4, in the absence of a confirmed case, the Department of Health (DH) launched a contingency plan to upgrade the response level from "alert" to "serious."
几天后，香港修例以完善新型肺炎的呈报。
A few days later, Hong Kong amended its regulations to improve reporting of new pneumonia.
香港政府发言人表示，将“严重新型传染性病原体呼吸系统病”纳入法定须呈报的传染病，提高监测此疾病的能力。
A Hong Kong Government spokesman said that the introduction of SARS into the statutory notifiable infectious disease would enhance the ability to monitor the disease.
全文3084字，阅读约需6分钟1月23日凌晨，香港公布了第二宗高度疑似新型冠状病毒感染个案。
Hong Kong announces the second case of a highly suspected coronavirus infection in the early morning hours of January 23, 2008.
病人是一名59岁香港男性居民，曾于1月10日至19日赴武汉看望父母。
The patient, a 59-year-old male resident of Hong Kong, visited his parents in Wuhan from January 10 to 19.
就在前一晚，香港相关部门召开记者会介绍了首宗高度疑似感染个案情况。
Just the night before, Hong Kong authorities held a press conference to introduce the first case of highly suspected infection.
根据香港卫生署卫生防护中心通报，自2019年12月31日至2020年1月22日，共接获135宗符合呈报准则的怀疑个案。
According to the Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health of Hong Kong, 135 suspected cases meeting the reporting criteria were received from 31 December 2019 to 22 January 2020.
1月21日中午至1月22日中午，共接报17宗疑似案例，其中就包括首宗高度疑似案例。
From noon on 21 January to noon on 22 January, 17 suspected cases were reported, including the first high-level suspected case.
23日，截至发稿前，香港电台网站援引香港卫生署消息称，香港2例高度疑似新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎病例被确诊。
At the time of writing, the RTHK website quoted the Hong Kong Department of Health (DH) as saying two cases of pneumonia in Hong Kong with a high suspected new coronavirus infection had been confirmed.
随着春节假期的到来，赴港旅客增多，香港的防疫体系再次面临考验。
With the coming of the Spring Festival holiday, Hong Kong's epidemic prevention system is once again facing a test.
▲1月23日，香港尖沙咀弥敦道附近药店所售口罩，50枚装一次性口罩售价在150港元左右。
On 23 January, 50 disposable masks sold at a pharmacy near Nathan Road, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong, cost about HK $150.
新京报记者 李玉坤 摄━━━━━“一天卖出400盒口罩”1月23日，记者所入住的尖沙咀某酒店前台已经戴口罩服务。
Sell 400 boxes of masks a day. On January 23, the front desk of a hotel in Tsim Sha Tsui, where reporters were staying, was wearing a mask service.
问及原因，他表示，听说香港已经有一例确诊病例。
Asked why, he said he had heard of one confirmed case in Hong Kong.
事实上，当时有两例高度疑似待确认。
In fact, there were two high-level suspicions pending confirmation.
记者走访了附近的药店，发现很多药店已经没有口罩出售，部分有售的药店，口罩价格明显比两天前高出许多。
The reporter visited the nearby drugstore, found that many pharmacies no longer sold masks, some pharmacies for sale, the price of masks significantly higher than two days ago.
其中一家药店50枚装的一次性口罩，售价是168港元；3D立体口罩5枚装的售价是128港元。
One pharmacy sold 50 disposable masks for HK $168 and three-dimensional masks for HK $128 each.
另一家50枚装的一次性口罩是138港元。
Another 50-piece disposable mask is HK $138.
口罩的售价每天都在上涨。
The price of masks goes up every day.
2天前，记者在铜锣湾某店，还可以以20港元的价格购入10枚。
Two days ago, we were able to buy 10 more units at a Causeway Bay store for HK $20.
当地媒体1月22日报道，尖沙咀加连威老道及加拿芬道一带药房一盒50枚的外科口罩“加价”至128元。
A box of 50 surgical masks was "marked up" to $128 at Galenway Road and Carnarvon Road pharmacy in Tsim Sha Tsui, local media reported on Tuesday.
“一天就卖出超过300盒外科口罩和100盒N95口罩，供应商来货价格平均上涨了3至8倍，所以只好加价卖。
More than 300 surgical masks and 100 boxes of N95 face masks were sold in a single day, and suppliers' prices rose an average of three to eight times, so we had to raise prices.
”药房职员说。
"said the drugstore clerk.
近两日，因确诊病例突然增加不少，公共场所佩戴口罩的市民也明显多了起来。
Over the past two days, the number of confirmed cases has risen sharply, as has the number of people wearing masks in public places.
1月23日9时许，地铁荃湾线有近半数乘客都佩戴了口罩，远多于1月20日。
At about 9: 00 a.m. on January 23, nearly half of the passengers on the Tsuen Wan MTR line were wearing masks, far more than on January 20.
地铁的引导员也戴上了口罩。
The subway conductor also put on a mask.
▲1月23日，荃湾线尖沙咀站，地铁引导员和多数乘客都已配套口罩。
On January 23, the Tsuen Wan Line at Tsim Sha Tsui Station, MTR Guide and most passengers were fitted with masks.
新京报记者 李玉坤 摄市民防范意识的增强，或许始于1月22日。
Li Yukun, a reporter for the Beijing News, may have stepped up public awareness since January 22.
当天，香港爆出首名高度疑似感染者。
Hong Kong blasted the first person to be highly suspected of infection.
当晚，香港食物及卫生局局长陈肇始和相关负责人召开记者会，公布了这名患者赴港的详细活动轨迹。
At a press conference that evening, the Secretary for Food and Health, Mr Chan Siu-kwong, announced the patient's itinerary to Hong Kong at a press conference.
根据通报，患者39岁，武汉来港游客，1月21日从武汉乘G1015高铁抵深圳北，座位3号车10D；当晚19:35乘G5607高铁到达香港西九龙站，座位2号车2D。
On January 21, Wuhan, a 39-year-old visitor from Wuhan, arrived in Shenzhen North on the G1015 high-speed rail from Wuhan, taking the G1015 high-speed train to the north of Shenzhen.
香港卫生署为此专门设立热线，呼吁乘搭有关高铁的人士致电21251122。
A hotline has been set up by the Department of Health to call 2125 1122.
香港卫生署署长陈汉仪表示，“该病例的前后两行乘客，属于紧密接触者，需要隔离”。
"The two lines of passengers in the case are in close contact and need to be quarantined," said the Director of Health, Ms CHAN HAN-yee.
23日凌晨，香港卫生署公布另一名高度疑似病例的活动轨迹。
The Department of Health announced the trajectory of another highly suspected case in the early morning of March 23.
患者是一名56岁男子，香港居民，1月10日独自前往武汉，19日由武汉乘坐中国国际航空CA8279航班前往深圳，同日经罗湖口岸乘坐港铁回港。
The patient, a 56-year-old Hong Kong resident, left for Wuhan on January 10 and travelled to Shenzhen by Air China Flight CA8279 on 19 January and returned to Hong Kong by rail from Lo Wu port on the same day.
当天上午10点半，香港卫生防护中心传染病处就通报，两宗高度怀疑新型冠状病毒感染肺炎个案，暂追踪到3名密切接触者，其中两人是医护人员，另一人是第二例患者的太太，稍后会安排隔离。
At 10: 30 a.m. on the same day, the Infectious Diseases Service of the Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Hong Kong Centre for Health Protection (CHP) informed the CHP that two highly suspected cases of coronavirus infection were temporarily traced to three close contacts, two of whom were medical staff and the other was the wife of a second patient.
▲1月22日晚，香港食物及卫生局局长陈肇始会见记者，介绍一宗高度疑似病例情况。
On the evening of 22 January, the Secretary for Food and Health, Mr Matthew Chan, met with the press to introduce a highly suspected case.
新京报记者 李玉坤 摄━━━━━曾被指“过度反应”在内地尚未通报多少确诊案例时，香港就开始通报疑似病例，且数量惊人，还因此被指“过度反应”。
2007-9-24 16: 00 (Li Yukun, Newspaper Beijing News) 2007-09-03 16: 07 (Li Yukun) When the mainland has not yet notified many confirmed cases, Hong Kong has started to report a staggering number of suspected cases, and has been accused of "over-reaction."
1月19日，香港通报疑似病例数量超过100人，当时除武汉外，少有其他城市通报确诊病例。
On January 19, Hong Kong reported more than 100 suspected cases, with few other cities, except Wuhan, reporting confirmed cases.
去年12月30日，武汉首次通报不明原因肺炎，27个病例中有7人病情严重。
On December 30, 2007, Wuhan first reported pneumonia due to unknown causes, with 7 out of 27 cases seriously ill.
次日，香港食物及卫生局局长陈肇始在记者会上表示，各出入境口岸加强健康监察措施，转移怀疑个案至公立医院接受隔离治疗，并致函各私家医生和私家医院。
The following day, the Secretary for Food and Health, Mr Matthew Chan, told a press conference that health surveillance measures had been stepped up at the entry and exit points to divert suspected cases to public hospitals for isolation treatment, and letters had been written to private doctors and hospitals.
1月4日，在尚无确诊病例的情况下，香港卫生署启动应变计划，将应变等级从“戒备”升为“严重”。
On January 4, in the absence of a confirmed case, the Department of Health (DH) launched a contingency plan to upgrade the response level from "alert" to "serious."
几天后，香港修例以完善新型肺炎的呈报。
A few days later, Hong Kong amended its regulations to improve reporting of new pneumonia.
香港政府发言人表示，将“严重新型传染性病原体呼吸系统病”纳入法定须呈报的传染病，提高监测此疾病的能力。
A Hong Kong Government spokesman said that the introduction of SARS into the statutory notifiable infectious disease would enhance the ability to monitor the disease.
1月20日，武汉通报，截至前一天22时累计报告新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎病例198例，已治愈出院25例，死亡3例。
On January 20, Wuhan announced that as of 2200 hours the previous day, 198 cases of pneumonia with new coronavirus infection had been reported, 25 cases had been cured and 3 cases had died.
北京和广东也在同天通报确诊病例。
Beijing and Guangdong also reported confirmed cases on the same day.
当天，香港更新“严重新型传染性病原体呼吸系统病”呈报准则：出现发烧及急性呼吸道感染征状或肺炎的病人，病发前14天如果曾到访湖北省，曾到访内地医院，或者曾与新型冠状病毒确诊个案于其出现病征时有密切接触的，都须呈报。
The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health (DH) today (May 12) reminded people to observe good personal hygiene and to observe good personal hygiene.
在这样的筛查标准下，香港接获的疑似病例数很快升至135例。
Under these screening criteria, the number of suspected cases in Hong Kong quickly rose to 135.
1月21日，在广东省新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情新闻发布会后，有港媒追问钟南山，为何香港疑似病例有100多例，广东只有10多例。
On January 21, after a press conference on the new coronavirus pneumonia in Guangdong Province, the Hong Kong media asked Zhong Nan Shan why there were more than 100 suspected cases in Hong Kong and just over 10 cases in Guangdong.
钟南山表示，不能仅凭到过武汉就怀疑是病例。
Zhong Nan Shan said, can not just go to Wuhan on suspicion of a case.
不过，他同时表示，早发现、早诊断、还有治疗和隔离，这是最有效、最原始的防控办法。
However, he said early detection, early diagnosis, treatment and isolation were the most effective and primitive methods of control.
根据香港每日情况通报，每名疑似病例都会写明接诊医院和阳性检测结果，大多数疑似病例为甲流、乙流、人类鼻病毒等。
According to the Hong Kong Daily Circular, every suspected case is marked with hospital admission and positive test results. The majority of suspected cases are influenza A, B, human rhinovirus, etc.
▲1月21日，香港西九龙高铁口岸，香港卫生署工作人员在对旅客进行体温筛查。
On 21 January, staff of the Hong Kong Department of Health (DH) conducted a temperature screening at the West Kowloon High Rail Port in Hong Kong.
新京报记者 李玉坤 摄━━━━━迅速应对在这场疫情应对中，香港反应迅速。
A quick response to the epidemic Hong Kong has been quick to respond to the epidemic.
1月9日，内地实验室取得新型冠状病毒的全基因组序列，香港卫生防护中心就向国家卫健委联系，以取得新型冠状病毒的基因排序，提供针对性的测试。
The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Hong Kong Centre for Health Protection (CHP) contacted the National Health Council (NCHP) on January 9 to obtain a gene sequencing for the new coronavirus and provide targeted testing.
针对各交通口岸的防控，早在10几天前，香港卫生防护中心就要求对所有出入境管制站加强为旅客作体温监测，并增加抽检安排，包括香港机场和高铁站。
As early as 10 days ago, the Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Hong Kong Centre for Health Protection (CHP) called for stepped-up surveillance of passengers at all immigration control points and increased sampling arrangements, including the Hong Kong Airport and the MTR stations.
1月20日午夜防控升级，香港要求所有从武汉搭乘飞机抵港的旅客填写健康申报表。
Hong Kong requires all passengers arriving by air from Wuhan to complete a health declaration at midnight on January 20.
除机场外，所有由武汉进入香港的港口都已设置体温监测仪。
In addition to the airport, all ports that enter Hong Kong from Wuhan have set up temperature monitors.
记者1月21日在香港西九龙高铁站发现，大陆海关卫生检疫部门在出境前发出提示，旅客有发热、头痛、咳嗽、咽痛、腹泻等传染病症状，应主动申报并接受检查。
The Health and Quarantine Department of the Mainland Customs and Excise Department issued a reminder on January 21 at the West Kowloon High Speed Rail Station in Hong Kong. Travellers with fever, headache, cough, sore throat, diarrhea and other infectious diseases should voluntarily report and undergo inspection.
随通道入境香港之后，香港卫生署多名工作人员手持体温探测仪，对入境人士进行体温筛查。
Following the passage to Hong Kong, a number of staff of the Hong Kong Department of Health (DH) conducted temperature screening with thermometers.
不过筛查频次并不高，记者前后旅客均未被要求体温筛查。
However, the frequency of screening is not high, reporters before and after the passengers were not required to temperature screening.
入境处柜台也写有提示：如出现发烧，以及于病发前14天内曾到访武汉的旅客，请在柜台处联系香港卫生署职员。
Visitors with fever and those who have visited Wuhan within 14 days before the onset of illness are advised to contact the staff of the Hong Kong Department of Health at the counter.
正是西九龙高铁站的体温筛查，发现了香港首例高度疑似病例。
It was temperature screening at West Kowloon High Speed Rail Station that revealed the first highly suspected case in Hong Kong.
这名39岁的男子，1月21日晚搭乘G5607高铁从深圳北到香港西九龙站，因体温异常被送医排查。
The 39-year-old man took the G5607 high-speed train from Shenzhen North to West Kowloon, Hong Kong, on the evening of January 21.
▲1月23日，香港政府和立法会附近升降梯，写有“按钮及扶手每日消毒3次”。
On 23 January, the Hong Kong Government and the Legislative Council lifted the escalator with the words "three times a day to disinfect buttons and handrails."
新京报记者 李玉坤 摄━━━━━被SARS重创过的城市这场疫情，不可避免地让人想到SARS。
Li Yukun, journalist with the Beijing News The SARS-battered city This outbreak is inevitably reminiscent of SARS.
17年前，香港是SARS的重灾区，教训惨重。
Seventeen years ago, Hong Kong was the epicentre of SARS.
世界各地总计确诊8096例SARS病例，744人死亡。
A total of 8,096 SARS cases and 744 deaths were diagnosed worldwide.
其中，中国内地死亡349人，香港死亡300人。
Of these, 349 died in mainland China and 300 in Hong Kong.
显然，香港接受了教训。
Clearly, Hong Kong has learned its lesson.
至今，香港许多楼宇电梯的按钮、护栏等几乎所有公共表面都会进行消毒处理，并标明每日消毒次数。
To date, nearly all public surfaces such as elevator buttons and fences in many buildings in Hong Kong have been disinfected and marked daily.
在香港政府附近的室外升降机和扶梯处，戴着口罩，依然能闻到84消毒液的味道。
In outdoor lifts and escalators near the Hong Kong government, wearing masks still smelled of disinfectant 84.
负责消毒的工作人员告诉记者，他们每天要擦拭三次，使用1比99的消毒液。
Staff in charge of disinfection told reporters that they had to wipe it three times a day, using 1: 99 disinfectant.
10时开始，两人在楼梯顶端开始擦拭，并躲避过往行人，10分钟后消毒完成，前往下一个地点。
At 1000 hours, the two men began to wipe at the top of the stairs and to avoid passers-by, disinfecting the area 10 minutes later and proceeding to the next location.
除了SARS，禽流感、MERS（中东呼吸综合征）都曾“造访”这座城市。
In addition to SARS, Avian Influenza and MERS have all visited the city.
香港对二者也无时无刻不在提防。
Hong Kong is always on guard against both.
就在每天通报新型冠状病毒感染情况的同时，香港卫生署卫生防护中心也通报了一起MERS疑似案例。
The Centre for Health Protection (CHP) of the Department of Health of Hong Kong (DH) has also reported a suspected case of a new coronavirus infection.
经初步化验，证实对中东呼吸综合征冠状病毒呈阴性反应。
After preliminary laboratory tests, confirmed to the Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus negative response.
22日的记者会上，香港食物及卫生局局长陈肇始透露，针对新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情，香港康文署已初步预留两个度假营作为“隔离营”。
The Secretary for Food and Health, Mr Matthew Chan, said at a press conference today (February 22) that the LCSD had initially reserved two holiday camps for the new coronavirus pneumonia as "quarantining camps."
一旦出现确诊个案，病人的紧密接触者需要隔离。
Once a confirmed case has emerged, the patient's close contacts need to be isolated.
麦理浩夫人度假村就是被预留的“隔离营”之一，据当地媒体报道，目前已有大批警员在度假村外驻守。
The Lady MacLehose Holiday Village is one of the "quarantined" camps reserved for a large number of police outside the resort, according to local media reports.
面对有媒体指责香港政府在新型肺炎事态上反应过慢，陈肇始表示，“绝对不会同意这个说法，香港的防疫措施已经提前了三步。
"In the face of media criticism that Hong Kong's government has been slow to respond to the new pneumonia situation, Chen said," I would definitely not agree that Hong Kong's vaccination measures are three steps ahead of schedule. "
”新京报记者 李玉坤编辑 陈思 校对 郭利琴值班编辑吾彦祖聚焦肺炎疫情：可能存在持续人传人，武汉市长呼吁减少人员流动武汉公交地铁今日停运，机场火车站离汉通道关闭从SARS到新型肺炎：有些人怎么就戒不掉这口“野味”?本文未经新京报书面授权不得转载使用欢迎朋友圈分享。
Wu Liqin, editor of the Beijing News Li Yukun, proofread by Chen Yucun, editor of the Beijing News, focused on pneumonia: there may be a continuing human-to-human transmission, Wuhan city chief called for a reduction in passenger flow.
